description: This is it – the grand finale of “THE RETURN OF DR. WILY"! Dr. Wily has hidden himself in his latest fortress and surrounded himself with killer robots as he plots his counter-attack. Can Mega Man breach the defenses and stop the mad scientist in time? Maybe not alone – but the Original Robot Masters have got his back! It’s all-out robot warfare in the explosive conclusion!
name: The Return of Doctor Wily, Part Four: Charge of the Light Brigade

description: As newly appointed class president, Kevin is in charge of selecting the theme for Riverdale High's prom. That's easy compared to the decision of who Kevin will take to the dance! And if things weren’t complicated enough, Kevin has a secret admirer hoping to be Kevin’s date…
name: May I Have This Dance?

description: In the aftermath of Peebri using Gina's singularity-powered server for online RPG hax, a clever little intruder has found her way into the lab—from another time! Under Brianna,Charlotte and Pini's interrogation, she claims to be Brianna and Zan's daughter from the future, but with all the other wild stories she's telling, can they believe her?

Jumpin' jacksnipes! Don Rosa's first Donald Duck tales are back in print! First up, Dynamic Don serves up his 'Return to Plain Awful' with Donald in search of square eggs with Uncle Scrooge and Flintheart Glomgold in tow! Next, our dashing duck fights it out with uber-lucky Gladstone in 'Oolated Luck' and 'Give Unto Others.' Experience jerky Neighbor Jones in 'Recalled Wreck,' and his own super-smart nephews in 'Mythological Menagerie' and 'Making the Grade!' All this plus other timeless tales including 'Fit to be Pied,' 'Rocket Reverie,' 'Forget me Not,' 'Star-Struck Duck,' 'Metaphorically Spanking,' 'The Crocodile Collector' and the rare Christmas classic 'Fir-Tree Fracas.' Including a cover gallery and ducky behind-the-scenes details never before told.

Story Titles

  • "Mythological Menagerie" - Story and art by Don Rosa (Walt Disney's Comics and Stories 523, October 1987)
  • "Recalled Wreck" - Story and art by Don Rosa (Walt Disney's Comics and Stories 524, December 1987)
  • "Fit To Be Pied" - Story and art by Don Rosa (Walt Disney's Comics and Stories 526, February 1988)
  • 'Fir-Tree Fracas" - Story and art by Don Rosa (Mickey and Donald 1, March 1988)
  • "Oolated Luck" - Story and art by Don Rosa (Walt Disney's Comics and Stories 528, April 1988)
  • "Rocket Reverie" - Story by Gary Leach, art by Don Rosa (Donald Duck Adventures [series 1] 5, July 1988)
  • "Metaphorically Spanking - Story and art by Don Rosa (Walt Disney's Comics and Stories 513, August 1988)
  • "The Crocodile Collector" - Story and art by Don Rosa (Donald Duck Adventures [series 1] 8, October 1988)
  • "Return to Plain Awful" - Story and art by Don Rosa (Donald Duck Adventures [series 1] 12, May 1989)
  • "The Starstruck Duck" - Story and scribbles by Don Rosa (Unfinished story, 1989)
  • "Give Unto Others" - Story by Arno Buitink, art by Don Rosa (Mickey and Donald 17, March 1990)
  • "Forget Me Not" - Story by Ruud Straatman, art by Don Rosa (Donald Duck 278, March 1990)
  • "Making the Grade" - Story by Jan Kruse, art by Don Rosa (Walt Disney's Comics and Stories 547, April 1990)
name: Vol. 1

description:
1. Turtle Jokes

2. The Time Machine

3. Side Show

4. The Bubble Blowers

5. Build Your Very Own Time Machine
name: The Time Machine

person_credits.name: Fred Schrier
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: It's trains and brains! Four would-be bounty hunters find themselves on a runaway train overrun by zombies and they must find a way off without unleashing the undead on an unsuspecting town!

Trash-collecting bear by day, crime-fighting martial artist by night. Dead Pooh protects the citizens of Hundred Acre Woodland City from the menace of the Candy King. In the best traditions of parody, Comi-Kazi presents the latest hero to arise to confront the forces of darkness for truth, justice...and a jar of hunny!

In 'Day Off/Off Day,' The Krusty Krab is under siege by SpongeBob! Krabs must keep the humble fry cook from entering the restaurant or (horrors!) face a modest fine for working his employees too hard. But a determined SpongeBob can get through any defenses that Krabs concocts. How far will Krabs go to keep him out? Also, Patrick and SpongeBob face the open road in big rigs. All this plus a pin-up, a choose-your-path comic of Squidward's nightmares, a page of aquatic facts, and a knockout back cover written by Joey Weiser!
name: Day Off/Off Day

description: SpongeBob journeys to an alternate dimension in 'Bikini Bottom 2' and encounters a very familiar - and yet startlingly different - cast of characters! In 'Squidward Saves Television,' Squidward takes over SpongeBob's favorite shows in order to bring a little class to television. Yeah, that'll work! Plus: a cover pin-up, 'SpongeFunnies' by James Kochalka, a painted back cover by Julie Wilson, and an interactive comic that invites readers to draw Mr. Krabs' tattoos!
name: Bikini Bottom 2 / Squidward Saves Television

description: In 'Missing Man,' SpongeBob, Patrick, and Barnacle Boy go on a desperately dumb search for a wayward Mermaid Man, annoying the hero's entire rogues gallery along the way. And SpongeBob becomes the champion of an underground civilization living beneath the Krusty Krab in 'Look Out Below.' Also, Gary heaves a hairball, courtesy of James Kochalka (Dragon Puncher), and Squidward's clarinet playing gets an assist from Bob Flynn (Heeby Jeeby Comics). All this plus a Scott Shaw! (Simpsons Comics) ad-parody and a pin-up of this issue's sword-and-spongery cover!
name: Missing Man / Look Out Below

description: Patrick and SpongeBob's kelp karpet sleds go really fast - and in 'Slip-Sledding Away,' SpongeBob finds a way to make them go even faster! Soon the friends find themselves sledding to a mysterious, faraway retirement community. In 'Recipe For Success,' Plankton finally puts his genius to work and creates a delicious secret formula of his own. Is this the end of The Krusty Krab? All this plus SpongeBob's unique solution to a toothache; a cover pin-up; and more!
name: Slip-Sledding Away / Recipe for Success

description: Despite the cover looking a lot like Doctor Solar might appear within, the Mighty Heroes Annual contains the adventures of Roldan and Astroman.
